<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFF2D8EB1FCBCFEEA" pageId="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFF2D8EB1FCBCFEEA" blockId="9.[173,660,1442,1729]" lastBlockId="9.[707,1194,194,879]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF2D8EB1FEDCF941" bold="true" box="[197,301,1682,1703]" pageId="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Specimens of this species have the pronotum and elytral disc mostly or totally black. These characteristics will distinguish the members of this species from others in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C719CFCFFABAB0BFBC988FFFB58FF17" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[1057,1193,220,241]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maracayensis">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFBC988FFFB58FF17" box="[1057,1193,220,241]" italics="true" pageId="9">maracayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFD338931FB69FCE3" pageId="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338931FBB0FD7D" blockId="9.[707,1194,194,879]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338931FC63FEC1" bold="true" box="[731,914,274,295]" pageId="9">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFBE98931FBABFEC1" box="[1025,1114,274,295]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFD2B890FFCE1FEA7" box="[707,784,300,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFCF3890FFCA2FEA7" bold="true" box="[795,851,300,321]" pageId="9">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFC75890FFC03FEA7" box="[925,1010,300,321]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="25.[197,238,1484,1503]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,193,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-88@25.[173,1194,192,1461]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figs. 116–120. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 116) P. opsus; 117) P. pallidus; 118) P. ostrinus; 119) P. corumba;" pageId="9">Fig. 120</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFC14890FFB80FEA7" bold="true" box="[1020,1137,300,321]" pageId="9">Integument</emphasis>
: Cranium mostly light brown, vertex and upper epicranium black; antenna black; pronotum mostly black, 2 light brown maculae near anterior margin; elytra black; femora mostly yellow, extremities of femora and tibiae black; pterothorax and abdomen black. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFCAB89EFFC8AFE07" bold="true" box="[835,891,460,481]" pageId="9">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes not as wide as frons (10:13); funicular antennomeres moderately expanded, 7 
<superScript id="7C044A37FFABAB0BFCD389DFFCB8FDEC" attach="left" box="[827,841,508,522]" fontSize="6" pageId="9">th</superScript>
antennomere not particularly long. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD2B8A38FCE1FDD6" bold="true" box="[707,784,539,560]" pageId="9">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum subquadrate (34:35), lateral tubercle very prominent; epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFC3F8A48FBCDFD66" bold="true" box="[983,1084,619,640]" pageId="9">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Tegminal lobes and phallic apex well-developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338A83FCBFFD36" blockId="9.[707,1194,194,879]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338A83FCCEFD53" bold="true" box="[731,831,672,693]" pageId="9">Variation.</emphasis>
The specimens before me are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338AF6FB69FCE3" blockId="9.[707,1194,194,879]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338AF6FC72FD0C" bold="true" box="[731,899,725,746]" pageId="9">Natural History.</emphasis>
All specimens were collected in October, two at 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFC938AD3FC3AFCE3" box="[891,971,752,773]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="9" unit="m" value="1900.0">1,900 m</quantity>
and one at 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFBA98AD3FB62FCE3" box="[1089,1171,752,773]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.936" pageId="9" unit="m" value="1936.0">1,936 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFD338B29FB5BFCF9" box="[731,1194,778,799]" pageId="9" type="distribution">
