</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFD338B06FB72FC89" pageId="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338B06FB72FC89" blockId="9.[707,1194,194,879]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338B06FCA6FCDC" bold="true" box="[731,855,805,826]" pageId="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
T h e t r i v i a l n a m e 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFBA08B06FB58FCDC" box="[1096,1193,805,826]" italics="true" pageId="9">p ro l a t u s</emphasis>
(= extended) is a Latin adjective that refers to the comparatively slender body form of this beetle.
</paragraph>
